sult of a year-long project by the Open Society Institute to examine and reappraise this tumultuous century. A cohort of young scholars with backgrounds in history, anthropology, political science, and comparative literature were brought together for this undertaking. The studies invite attention to fascism, socialism, and liberalism as well as nationalism and Communism. While most chapters deal with war and confrontation, they focus rather on the remembrance of such conflicts in shaping today's ideology and national identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aNationalismxBalkan Peninsula. 0aNationalismexBalkans. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / General.2bisacsh  aBalkan, Childhood, Communism, Historiography, Identity, Ideology, Nationalism, Political studies.1 aAustin, Robert C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiondich, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrkljačić, Maja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBulatović, Marko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErdei, Ildiko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrusetta, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuentcheva, Rossitza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIordachi, Constantin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJović, Dejan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLampe, John R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLampe, John R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMazower, Mark, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPrlenda, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://